## Problem

Only 4 files in firmware use printf/ESP_LOG. 104 functions in firmware have no structured logging. Issues:
- Hard to debug in production (can't enable/disable log levels)
- No timestamp or component identifiers
- Logs mixed with debug output

## Solution

Create `firmware/components/logging/log.h` (ADDITIVE, non-breaking):

```c
/**
 * @file log.h
 * @brief Centralized logging for firmware (ADDITIVE, non-breaking)
 */

#ifndef LOG_H
#define LOG_H

#include <stdbool.h>
#include <stdint.h>
#include "esp_log.h"

/* Log levels */
typedef enum {
    LOG_LEVEL_ERROR = 0,
    LOG_LEVEL_WARN = 1,
    LOG_LEVEL_INFO = 2,
    LOG_LEVEL_DEBUG = 3,
} log_level_t;

/* Default log level (can be changed at runtime) */
extern log_level_t g_log_level;

/**
 * @brief Set global log level
 */
static inline void log_set_level(log_level_t level) {
    g_log_level = level;
}

/**
 * @brief Check if log level is enabled
 */
static inline bool log_should_log(log_level_t level) {
    return level <= g_log_level;
}

/* Logging macros (ADDITIVE - don't replace existing code) */
#define LOG_ERROR(tag, fmt, ...) \
    if (log_should_log(LOG_LEVEL_ERROR)) { \
        ESP_LOGE(tag, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
    }

#define LOG_WARN(tag, fmt, ...) \
    if (log_should_log(LOG_LEVEL_WARN)) { \
        ESP_LOGW(tag, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
    }

#define LOG_INFO(tag, fmt, ...) \
    if (log_should_log(LOG_LEVEL_INFO)) { \
        ESP_LOGI(tag, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
    }

#define LOG_DEBUG(tag, fmt, ...) \
    if (log_should_log(LOG_LEVEL_DEBUG)) { \
        ESP_LOGV(tag, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
    }

/* Safe to include with or without existing ESP_LOG */
#ifdef CONFIG_ESP_LOG
/* ESP_LOG already included by ESP-IDF */
#else
/* Provide fallback for unit tests */
static inline void ESP_LOGE(const char *tag, const char *fmt, ...) {
    // printf-based fallback
}
static inline void ESP_LOGW(const char *tag, const char *fmt, ...) {
    // printf-based fallback
}
static inline void ESP_LOGI(const char *tag, const char *fmt, ...) {
    // printf-based fallback
}
static inline void ESP_LOGV(const char *tag, const char *fmt, ...) {
    // printf-based fallback
}
#endif

#endif /* LOG_H */
```

**Migration path (OPTIONAL, not required):**

Phase 1: Add logging utility (no code changes required)
Phase 2: Gradually migrate to LOG_* macros over time

